THE formal bail application of a 32-years-old man bust for the illegal possession of drugs has been postponed until Monday 18 January. The accused appeared before the Middelburg Magistrates Court on Thursday 14 January. Mpumalanga Hawks spokeswoman Captain Lucy Sekgotodi said the accused was arrested by the Hawks, assisted by members of the Middelburg Public Order Policing, K-9 and Witbank Crime Intelligence. He was bust for illegal possession of drugs on Wednesday 13 January during the multi-disciplinary search and seizure operation in Mhluzi. “A sting operation was conducted in the early hours of the morning where drugs and cash were found in the suspect’s possession. “The drugs and cash were subsequently seized for further investigation. He’s expected to appear again on Monday in the Middelburg Magistrate Court,” said Sekgotodi.  